  "prompt": "How do I register my business in the U.K.?",
  "response": "To register a business in the UK, follow these steps:\n\n1. Choose a business structure:\n- Sole trader\n- Partnership\n- Limited company\n- Limited liability partnership (LLP)\n\n2. Register with Companies House:\n- For limited companies and LLPs, register online at gov.uk\n- Provide company name, address, directors, shareholders details\n- Pay registration fee (usually around \u00a312)\n\n3. Register for Corporation Tax:\n- Register within 3 months of starting business\n- Can do this online via gov.uk\n- Obtain a Unique Taxpayer Reference (UTR)\n\n4. Register for VAT (if applicable):\n- Mandatory if turnover exceeds \u00a385,000 annually\n- Can voluntarily register below this threshold\n\n5. Additional requirements:\n- Open a business bank account\n- Get business insurance\n- Register for PAYE if hiring employees\n\n6. Other considerations:\n- Obtain necessary licenses\n- Check local council regulations\n- Consider professional advice from accountant/lawyer\n\nSpecific steps might vary slightly depending on your business structure and sector. The gov.uk website provides comprehensive guidance for each business type.\n\nWould you like more details about a specific business structure?",
